```json
{
  "application": "Gromacs",
  "software": [
    "intel/2020.1",
    "impi/2018.4",
    "mkl/2020.1",
    "boost/1.75.0",
    "plumed/2.8.0",
    "gromacs/2021.4-plumed.2.8.0"
  ],
  "resources": {
    "time": "72 hours",
    "qos": "class_a",
    "cpus_per_task": 2,
    "ntasks_per_node": 24,
    "nodes": 4
  }
}
```

This script uses Gromacs, a molecular dynamics simulation software package. The script performs three simulations: NVT (constant volume and temperature), NPT (constant pressure and temperature), and an initial MD simulation. The script uses a variety of modules including Intel compiler, MPI, MKL, boost, plumed, and Gromacs. 

The script utilizes resources from the cluster, requesting 72 hours of wall time, "class_a" quality of service, 2 CPUs per task, 24 tasks per node, and 4 nodes.
